                            "schema_version": 1.1,
                            "value": "200 feet"
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "On a failed save, the harpoon becomes lodged in the target\u2019s body. The target can remove the harpoon with a DC 22 check to Escape or Force Open , but on a failure, the target takes 6d4 piercing damage. As long as the harpoon cannon bolt remains lodged, the target cannot move more than 200 feet away from the harpoon cannon. If the harpoon cannon bolt is embedded in a creature that isn\u2019t swimming, one member of the crew can attempt to Trip the creature by tugging on the rope if all other crew members Aid . On a failure, the bolt rips free, causing 4d4 piercing damage to the target but releasing it.",
